FuncDef: This command, when used without parameters, allows the operator to identify QoS match-criteria memory banks with one or more policies in overload in the system by slot number, FP number, type (IP-MAC or IPv6), SAP ingress, SAP egress, network, and direction (ingress or egress).

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the IOM slot number for the overload command. Values-1 to 10.
Specifies the FP number. Values-1 to 8.
Specifies the network policy ID. Values-1 to 65538.
Specifies the memory bank ingress or egress direction. Values-ingress or egress.
Specifies the SAP policy ID. Values-1 to 65535.
Specifies the SAP policy ID. Values-1 to 65535.
